<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05131d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05131d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05131d"> 131(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ophelia (Ophis serpent) / Trojan war / preda di guerra</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Homer&apos;s celebrate diviner, Calchas, interpreted the eight swallows and their mother who were devoured by the serpent as signifying the land of Troy which, at the end of nine years, would fall, and so the Greeks called the booty of war (preda di guerra) <i>opheleia</i> from <i>ophis</i> or &lsquo;serpent&rsquo;.]</font> <small> Giambattista Vico, <a name="VICO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VICO"><cite title="source">Principj di una Scienza Nuova</cite></a> (1836) III, XV</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
